{
  "texts": [
    "CASE is a corruption augmentation mechanism to the three rubrics in which AES is trained for essay scoring (Yoo et al. 2024).",
    "And, EssayCoT is an essay Chain-of-Thought which is used for feedback generation based on the essay scoring with zero-shot mechanism.",
    "BERT is employed for essay representation and ChatGPT for feedback generation.",
    "Fiacco et al. (2023) proposed a method that can be used to improve the interpretability of Longformer AES models by mapping relationships between feature groups and functional groups.",
    "The models in this work are rubric-based model that are trained on organization, main idea, support, and language traits."
  ]
}